<h2><strong>Why is my dryer making loud banging or thumping noises?</strong></h2>
<p>Loud banging or thumping noises coming from your dryer can be concerning and indicate that something is wrong. Here
  are some common reasons why your dryer might be making these noises and what you can do about it:</p>
<p>1. <strong>Unbalanced Load</strong>: If the load inside the dryer is unbalanced, it can cause the drum to spin
  unevenly, leading to loud banging noises. Try redistributing the clothes evenly inside the drum and running the dryer
  again.</p>
<p>2. <strong>Worn Drum Rollers</strong>: The drum rollers support the dryer drum and help it spin smoothly. Over time,
  these rollers can wear out and cause the drum to thump or bang as it rotates. Replacing worn drum rollers can resolve
  this issue.</p>
<p>3. <strong>Damaged Drum Belt</strong>: The drum belt is responsible for turning the drum. If the belt is damaged or
  worn out, it can cause the drum to make loud noises. Inspect the belt for signs of wear and replace it if necessary.
</p>
<p>4. <strong>Loose or Worn Drum Bearings</strong>: Drum bearings allow the drum to spin freely. If these bearings are
  loose or worn out, they can produce loud thumping or banging sounds. Replacing the drum bearings can fix this problem.
</p>
<p>5. <strong>Foreign Objects</strong>: Sometimes, small objects like coins or buttons can get trapped inside the drum
  or the drum's seal, causing loud noises when the dryer is in operation. Check the drum and remove any foreign objects.
</p>
<p>6. <strong>Faulty Idler Pulley</strong>: The idler pulley keeps tension on the drum belt. If the pulley is faulty or
  worn out, it can cause the belt to slip and produce loud noises. Replacing the idler pulley can help resolve this
  issue.</p>
